Exeter City sign Brentford winger Tony Yogane on loan
arts.sum: Diabate came on as a substitute in the closing stages of the midweek draw at Peterborough United, but that is his only action since returning to Valley Parade with City boss Gary Caldwell using other players out of position in the centre back roles instead. We’re working really hard on that but our goal return up until these last two games has been really quite good over that period of time through Christmas and up to now, so it’s not something that we’re concerned with.

arts.ttl: Exeter City hope to learn their lessons and get back to winning ways
arts.sum: Strange in that they didn’t play well, but neither did Peterborough, which is why it all felt like a missed opportunity for City to register a first win at a ground they have not won at since 1989. But as the Seasiders poured forward looking for a winner, their pressure paid off when James Husband headed in from a corner deep into stoppage time to deny City a point.
